channel.title: Dj java decompiler deleted my client files!
channel.description:
so. i had some kind of dj java decompiler. there's java class files that are memory or something. i was changing something and i accidently moved the client.java into config. but i set it back to it real place. and when i put my server back online all the new things i added to client.java were vanished and they were the old client.java. everytime i added something to client.java and compile nothing happens, nothing actually ever.
if i move or delete the decompiler of client.java and i restart server and it sais that the client isnt exsisting.
or do i have to delete the decompiler itself? please help me!
